channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [HIVE-19951] Vectorization: Need to disable encoded LLAP I/O for ORC when there is data type conversion (Schema Evolution)
item.description: Currently, reading encoded ORC data does not support data type conversion. So, encoded reading and cache populating needs to be disabled.
item.summary: Vectorization: Need to disable encoded LLAP I/O for ORC when there is data type conversion (Schema Evolution)

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Ok, pending new ORC release that contains ORC-380.

prasanth_j I'm considering committing this change first and creating a follow-on ticket to loosen up the restrictions by checking ORC-380's isOnlyImplicitConversion() method when the new ORC release goes out...
